sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1649000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The chimaera Cph8 is the phytochrome Cph1 fusing with a cyanobacterial photoreceptor EnvZ which can engineer a red light-regulated transcription system in E. coli, with the phycocyanobilin-biosynthesis genes (ho1 and pcyA). The promoter OmpC is repressed by the function of red light and activated by dark .
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang Yang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The source of this part comes from the kit plates
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The promoter of cph8 has not been designed so that users can choose suitable promoter for their projects.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K592018
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the red light sensor Cph8 with RBS.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The cph8 was taken from Tabor's pJT122 plasmid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Since Cph8 was considerably longer than the RBS added, sequencing was necessary to confirm the construct.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cph8
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is identical to BBa_I15010, the cph8 red light sensor. We were unable to transform BBa_I15010 from the the 2011 iGEM distribution kit. PCR attempts using VF2 and VR failed to amplify any DNA from the well sample. In the end, we chose to amplify cph8 from Jeffrey Tabor's pJT122 plasmid provided by Chris Voigt. The cph8 in pJT122 contained an internal PstI site, which was removed by point-mutagenesis. The resultant DNA sequence is identical to that of BBa_I15010.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The source DNA (pJT122) contained illegal restriction site (PstI) that had to be removed.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: OmpR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Positively regulated, OmpR-controlled promoter. This promoter is taken from the upstream region of ompC. Phosphorylated OmpR binds to the three operator sites and activates transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephen Lee, Roshan Kumar, Joe Levine, Ziyan Chu (Polkadorks, IAP 2004)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The promoter includes the three OmpR binding sites: C1, C2, and C3. The promoter starts at -107 and goes up to the transcriptional start site at +1.
An alternate version, BBa_R0083, cuts out the C2 and C3 sites.
The efficacy of this promoter versus the truncated ompC upstream region (BBa_R0083) or the ompF upstream region (BBa_R0084) is currently unknown.
